---
name: dcx-routines
description: Use dcx to manage BigQuery routines via the get, list commands. Generated from the BigQuery v2 Discovery API.
---

## When to use this skill

Use when the user asks about:
- "get a BigQuery routine"
- "list a BigQuery routine"
- "show me BigQuery routines"
- "what routines are in my project"

Do not use when the user wants analytics workflows (doctor, evaluate, get-trace) — use dcx-analytics instead.

## Prerequisites

Authentication: `dcx auth login` or set `DCX_PROJECT` / `DCX_TOKEN` environment variables.

Requires: `--project-id` and `--dataset-id`

## Commands

### routines get

Gets the specified routine resource by routine ID.

```bash
dcx routines get \
  --project-id <PROJECT_ID> \
  --dataset-id <DATASET_ID> \
  --routine-id <ROUTINE_ID> \
  [--read-mask <READ_MASK>] \
  [--dry-run] \
  [--format json|table|text]
```

| Flag | Required | Description |
|------|----------|-------------|
| `--project-id` | Yes | GCP project ID (global flag) |
| `--dataset-id` | Yes | BigQuery dataset (global flag) |
| `--routine-id` | Yes | Required |
| `--read-mask` | No | If set, only the Routine fields in the field mask are returned in the response |

### routines list

Lists all routines in the specified dataset. Requires the READER dataset role.

```bash
dcx routines list \
  --project-id <PROJECT_ID> \
  --dataset-id <DATASET_ID> \
  [--filter <FILTER>] \
  [--max-results <MAX_RESULTS>] \
  [--read-mask <READ_MASK>] \
  [--dry-run] \
  [--format json|table|text]
```

| Flag | Required | Description |
|------|----------|-------------|
| `--project-id` | Yes | GCP project ID (global flag) |
| `--dataset-id` | Yes | BigQuery dataset (global flag) |
| `--filter` | No | If set, then only the Routines matching this filter are returned |
| `--max-results` | No | The maximum number of results to return in a single response page |
| `--read-mask` | No | If set, then only the Routine fields in the field mask, as well as project_id, dataset_id and routine_id, are returne... |

## Decision rules

- Use `--dry-run` to see the API request without executing it
- Use `--format table` for scanning results visually in a terminal
- Use `--format json` when piping output to other tools or scripts
- Use `routines list` to discover available routines in a project
- Use `routines get` to inspect a specific routine's metadata

## Examples

```bash
# Get routines
dcx routines get \
  --project-id my-proj \
  --dataset-id my_dataset \
  --routine-id my_routine_id \
  --format table

# List routines
dcx routines list \
  --project-id my-proj \
  --dataset-id my_dataset \
  --format table

```

## Constraints

- These commands are generated from the BigQuery v2 Discovery API
- Only read operations are supported in Phase 2
- Nested response objects are summarized in table format; use `--format json` for full detail
- Reference objects (e.g. routinesReference) are automatically flattened in table output
